President Barack Obama has appointed N. Gunter Guy, Jr. as the State Representative for the Gulf Coast Ecosystem Restoration Task Force. The task force was established to coordinate restoration programs and projects in the Gulf Coast region. Guy is currently the Commissioner of the Alabama Department of Conservation and Natural Resources and has experience in advising on the management of natural resources. He previously worked as an attorney and served as the City Attorney for the City of Montgomery, Alabama. Guy holds a BS degree from Auburn University and a JD degree from Cumberland School of Law at Samford University.